      * CADCLI2.DAT SOMENTE OS CLIENTES DO SEXO MASCULINO.

        ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
            CONFIGURATION SECTION.
            SOURCE-COMPUTER. IBM-PC.
            OBJECT-COMPUTER. IBM-PC.
            SPECIAL-NAMES.   DECIMAL-POINT IS COMMA.

            INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
            FILE-CONTROL.
            SELECT CADCLI1 ASSIGN TO DISK
            ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
            SELECT CADCLI2 ASSIGN TO DISK
            ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

        DATA DIVISION.
            FILE SECTION.

            FD CADCLI1
               LABEL RECORD IS STANDARD
               VALUE OF FILE-ID IS "CADCLI1.DAT".
            01 REGCLI1.
               02 COD-ENT  PIC 9(05).
               02 NOME-ENT PIC X(20).
               02 SEXO-ENT PIC X(01).

            FD CADCLI2
               LABEL RECORD IS STANDARD
               VALUE OF FILE-ID IS "CADCLI2.DAT".
            01 REGCLI2.
               02 NOME-SAI PIC X(20).
               02 COD-SAI  PIC 9(05).

            WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
            77 FIM-ARQ PIC X(03) VALUE "NAO".
        
        PROCEDURE DIVISION.
        PGM.
            PERFORM INICIO.
            PERFORM PRINCIPAL UNTIL FIM-ARQ EQUAL "SIM".
            PERFORM TERMINO.
        STOP RUN.

        INICIO.
            OPEN INPUT  CADCLI1
                 OUTPUT CADCLI2.
            PERFORM LEITURA.

        LEITURA.
            READ CADCLI1 AT END MOVE "SIM" TO FIM-ARQ.

        GRAVACAO.
            IF SEXO-ENT IS NOT EQUAL TO "M" THEN EXIT SECTION.
            MOVE COD-ENT  TO COD-SAI.
            MOVE NOME-ENT TO NOME-SAI.
            WRITE REGCLI2.

        PRINCIPAL.
            PERFORM GRAVACAO.
            PERFORM LEITURA.

        TERMINO.
            CLOSE CADCLI1
                  CADCLI2.
